<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05020h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05020h">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05020h"> 20(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 1st Friday after 1 plenil. after / spring equinox</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Why should it <font color="green">[death of Christ]</font> be the <mark>first Friday after the first full moon after the spring equinox</mark>? <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Crucifixion] 304</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The Roman Church and the great majority of Christians celebrate the Pasch [Easter] on the Sunday after Nisan 14 &mdash; that is, on the Sunday following the first full moon [the <mark><i>plenilunium</i></mark>] after the vernal equinox, and on the previous Friday commemorate the memory of Christ&apos;s death. </mm> </dd></dl>
